### Summary of Document LEX540 Batch Report (Bangor, Batch 3)

This document is a two-page "IBM Batch Report" for Batch Number 3, from the Bangor Vote Collection Point (ID 2178) in NSW, part of Electoral Event ID 19694. The batch was created on 2016-06-10, and the report generated on 2016-06-15. It details the processing outcomes for 50 ballots within this specific batch.

The report provides a comprehensive breakdown of various ballot processing checks, including:
*   `QualityAssurance Checked`
*   `Initials Checked`
*   `Official Mark Checked`
*   `UnusualMarkings Checked`
*   `Formality Result Checked`
*   `Verification Action`
*   `Formality Reason Checked`
*   Multiple checks related to Above-the-Line (ATL) and Below-the-Line (BTL) preferences, including `Preferences Checked`, `Mismatches`, `Saved Checked`, `Breakdown Checked`, and `Formal Checked`.

Crucially, for all 50 ballots listed (Ballot 1 through Ballot 50), every single processing check across all categories indicates "OK". No entries for `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, or `BTL Mismatches` show "HAS ISSUES" or any associated alphanumeric codes.

### Relevance to FOI Request [LEX540]

This document is highly relevant to Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] as it is precisely one of the "IBM Batch Report" PDF files from 2016. It provides concrete insight into the ballot processing records sought.

While the FOI overview states that `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, and `BTL Mismatches` frequently show "HAS ISSUES" entries with alphanumeric codes in other reports, this particular document presents a *counter-example* where all 50 ballots in the batch were processed successfully without any detected issues or exceptions. This indicates that not all "IBM Batch Reports" contained anomalies and provides a baseline for comparison, demonstrating a "clean" batch where all automated and manual checks resulted in an "OK" status.

Considering this document as part of an FOI request, summarize the document and its relevance to the FOI request in markdown format. FYI the overview of the FOI request is: Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] sought documents related to 'IBM Outputs' from 2016, yielding 106 "IBM Batch Report" PDF files dated June 8, 10, and 15, 2016, categorized by Vote Collection Point and Batch Number. These detailed reports provide insights into ballot processing, including batch metadata, electoral event context, and specific ballot-level checks for formality, initials, marks, and preferences (ATL/BTL). While most entries indicate "OK" for successful processing, various checks, notably `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, and `BTL Mismatches`, frequently show "HAS ISSUES" entries, often accompanied by alphanumeric codes (e.g., D2, Y9, M1, U1), signifying specific anomalies or exceptions in the ballot processing.
